abstract: SNOW HILL, Md., June 19.--The jury in the case of Lilian Duer for the killing of Ella Hearn came into court at 9:15 A.M. to-day. The Courthouse was crowded. The panel was called, and in reply to the question of the Clerk, the jury announced that it had agreed upon a verdict. Granville Stokes, the foreman, when called upon for the verdict, answered: "Guilty of manslaughter, with recommendation to the mercy of the court."
